The reaſon wherefore the Members in the Houſe of Parliament were preferred in their Countreys ſuffrages to be their Judges, was for the opinion of their Wiſdom and Integrity above, at leaſt equal to others of the Countrey: Wiſdom conſiſts of Circumſpection, Diffidence, foreſight; 

                     〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
                  . Euripid. The French call Miſtruſt the Mother of Wiſdom. Diffidence eſpecially, as Integrity doth, of diſtributing and doing all men right.
